<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="302" pageId="1" pageNumber="299" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1474,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,1549,1575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Description.</emphasis>
Rostrum straight 0.65 times as long as carapace, reaching to midpoint of second segment of antennular peduncle (
<figureCitation box="[425,498,1586,1612]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A), with 3 postrostral teeth, posteriormost tooth not reaching midpoint of carapace, second and third tooth posterior of orbital margin (
<figureCitation box="[860,936,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
A–B), 4 teeth on rostrum proper; 4 ventral teeth; dorsal rostrum teeth with 1 stiff seta inserted between teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1474,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">
Carapace smooth, 1.4 times as long as high, posteroventral margin rounded; pterygostomial angle with pronounced acute tooth (
<figureCitation box="[443,510,1736,1762]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C). Eyes relatively large, not reaching dorsal margin of rostrum in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,225,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A). Antennal tooth pronounced, reaching to midpoint of cornea. Antennular peduncle as long as or just falling short of distal margin of scaphocerite; stylocerite reaching to midpoint of first segment (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1356,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
A, D); second segment about 1.7 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[769,852,1848,1874]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
C–D); third segment as long as second; lateral antennular flagellum long, with secondary ramus reduced to rudiment (
<figureCitation box="[997,1064,1885,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
E). Scaphocerite three times as long as wide, with slightly concave lateral margin; distolateral tooth overreaching blade (
<figureCitation box="[1195,1261,1922,1948]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1474,2023]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,252]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="1" pageNumber="299">
Pleura of first three abdominal somites with rounded margin; pleuron of fourth somite rounded, lacking sharp posterolateral tooth; pleuron of fifth somite with sharp posterolateral tooth; sixth somite with acute posteroventral tooth and acute posterolateral tooth (
<figureCitation box="[753,819,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="300">
Fig. 
<date box="[807,833,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="300">1I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Telson about 1.8 times as long as sixth abdominal somite, tapering posteriorly; dorsal surface with two pairs of spines (
<figureCitation box="[966,1033,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="300">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
G); posterior margin not medially acute, with pair of long slender spines each flanked by a much shorter spine.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="300" targetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1872,1991]" pageId="2" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1872,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="300">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[297,457,1872,1895]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[297,457,1872,1895]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="300">Lysmata rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[465,557,1872,1895]" pageId="2" pageNumber="300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5–6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A,C–I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K =0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,327]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,588]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="302" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">
Third maxilliped with exopod reaching to 0.65 of antepenultimate segment, tip of ultimate segment with 5 spines (3 large, 2 small), in addition to 3 subdistal ones (
<figureCitation box="[807,888,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B). Remainder of mouthparts typical for the genus. First pereiopod with simple chela (
<figureCitation box="[648,731,226,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
C, E), over-reaching distal margin of the scaphocerite when fully extended, carpus reaching or just overreaching first segment of antennular peduncle; ischium with row of spinules on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[507,577,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D); merus 1.6 times longer than carpus; propodus about 2.5 times as long as dactylus, 4.4 times as long as high (
<figureCitation box="[620,693,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
E). Second pereiopods slender, ending in small simple chelae (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
F, G); propodus about 2 times as long as dactylus, merus with 7 segments; carpus about twice as long as merus, with 15 segments (
<figureCitation box="[458,529,226,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" targetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1901,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1901,1925]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[293,448,1902,1925]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[293,448,1902,1925]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="301">Lysmata rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[456,545,1901,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="301" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H– I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,588]" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">
Third to fifth pereiopods similar, decreasing in length from third to fifth (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1145,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
H–I, K); third pereiopod reaching to mid-length of scaphocerite; merus with 3 spines; dactylus about 0.2 times length of propodus (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
H–I, K); distally biunguiculate, armed with 5 spines, dorsal unguis longer than ventral, flexor margin with 3 spinules, increasing in size from proximal to distal (
<figureCitation box="[836,906,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
J). Fourth and fifth pereiopod similar to third, with dactylus bearing 5 spines; merus with 4 spines (
<figureCitation box="[766,837,413,439]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1388,387,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,377,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, third maxilliped; B, same, tip of ultimate segment; C, first pereiopod; D same, detail of Ischium; E, same, detail of chela; F, second pereiopod; G, same, detail of chela; H, third pereiopod; I, fourth pereiopod; J, same, detail of dactylus; K, fifth pereiopod. Scales: A-C, F, H – I, K = 1 mm; D, E, G, J = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275823/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
H). First and second pleopods as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[1356,1417,413,439]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig.1</figureCitation>
J, K). Uropod as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[458,524,450,476]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[245,1371,355,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,342,1854]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: A, anterior carapace and frontal appendages, lateral view; B, carapace, lateral view; C, frontal region, dorsal view; D, antennule; E, antennular flagella; F, scaphocerite; G, telson; H, uropod; I, pleonites 5 – 6, lateral view; J, first pleopod; K, second pleopod. Scales: A, C – I = 1 mm; B = 2 mm; J, K = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275822/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,588]" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,355,487,513]" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Color in life.</emphasis>
Body translucent with red longitudinal and diagonal stripes, dorsal portion of the abdominal pleurons with three longitudinal red stripes reaching to the distal end of uropods and telson, first and third abdominal pleurons with transverse red bands; gonads and embryos bright green (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1181,562,588]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1181,1205]" captionTargetBox="[250,1341,645,1158]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[250,1341,645,1158]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lysmata rauli sp. nov., holotype, hermaphrodite, USNM 1130395: Live colour pattern." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275824/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="302">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
